362 teams. 26 missing teams added, 0 mismatches.\n\n- **`data/processed/team_games_2025.csv`**: Rebuilt from 351→364 teams. 13 missing teams (all MAC/OVC — Pac-12 dissolved so no longer a gap). 2 mismatches fixed (UCF, Nebraska each -1).\n\n- **`data/processed/team_games_2026.csv`**: Already had 365 teams. 1 mismatch fixed (Florida A&M: 32→31). 0 missing teams.\n\n- **`backend/main.py`**: FastAPI backend. Key endpoints:\n  - `GET /api/ratings/{season}` — queries `player_ratings` table with filters (position, team, min_rating, two_way). Returns up to 15,000 rows\n  - `GET /api/stats/{player_id}/{season}` — runs 4 separate queries (pergame, advanced, misc, ratings)\n  - `GET /api/search` — searches players by name\n  - `GET /api/stats/leaderboard/{season}` — top players by stat with whitelist security\n  - Uses `text()` from SQLAlchemy, `DecimalEncoder` for JSON\n\n- **`index.html`** (main frontend, `/Users/jimmyzhang/Development/realgm-scraper/index.html`):\n  - Pure HTML/JS, Tailwind-free (uses raw CSS), gradient purple background\n  - Table columns currently: Rank, Player, Team, Pos, GP, PPG, RPG, APG, Rating\n  - Loads all players via `GET /api/ratings/${currentSeason}?limit=15000`\n  - Player modal calls `GET /api/stats/${playerId}/${currentSeason}` — shows per-game, advanced, misc\n  - `API_BASE = 'http://localhost:8000/api'`\n  - Season selector: 2025-26, 2024-25, 2023-24, 2022-23, 2021-22\n  - Client-side filtering by position, team, min_rating, name search\n\n- **`player_stats_totals` table** (newly created):\n  ```sql\n  CREATE TABLE player_stats_totals (\n      id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n      player_id VARCHAR(20) REFERENCES players(player_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n      season VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,\n      age INTEGER, level VARCHAR(50), league_name VARCHAR(100),\n      team VARCHAR(100), class_year VARCHAR(50), stat_type VARCHAR(50),\n      gp INTEGER, gs INTEGER,\n      min NUMERIC(8,2), pts NUMERIC(8,2), fgm NUMERIC(8,2), fga NUMERIC(8,2),\n      fg_pct NUMERIC(5,4), fg3m NUMERIC(8,2), fg3a NUMERIC(8,2), fg3_pct NUMERIC(5,4),\n      ftm NUMERIC(8,2), fta NUMERIC(8,2), ft_pct NUMERIC(5,4),\n      off_reb NUMERIC(8,2), def_reb NUMERIC(8,2), trb NUMERIC(8,2),\n      ast NUMERIC(8,2), stl NUMERIC(8,2), blk NUMERIC(8,2), tov NUMERIC(8,2), pf NUMERIC(8,2),\n      created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,\n      UNIQUE (player_id, season, team, stat_type)\n  );\n  ```\n  Loaded 58,402 rows (42,824 D1), seasons 2015-16 through 2025-26.\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n\n- **Cloudflare blocking scraper**: Both `cloudscraper` (403) and headless Playwright blocked. Fix: use non-headless Playwright (`headless=False`).\n\n- **Pagination table index shift**: After clicking pagination, table data moved from `tables[1]` to `tables[2]` due to fixed-header plugin creating duplicate structure. Fix: use last table with a non-empty tbody (`for t in reversed(soup.find_all('table'))`).\n\n- **62 unrated 2021-22 players with valid stats**: Washington, Arizona, Murray State, Toledo, Western Michigan roster players (except the 5 specifically targeted from the qualified page) were never rated. The first batch only targeted 5 specific player IDs; the second batch's `new_teams` set didn't include those 5 teams. Fix: ran full missing-player calculation for 2021-22.\n\n- **player_stats_totals FK violations (20,702)**: `players` table only had 9,120 of 12,749 players. 3,629 players were fully scraped (in players.csv with complete bio) but never loaded into DB. Fix: loaded missing players with slim schema mapping (`player_id, full_name, position, height_ft, weight_lbs, hometown, birthdate`), then reloaded totals successfully.\n\n- **`player_stats_misc.hob` type error**: Column defined as `INTEGER` but CSV contains decimals (e.g., `0.026`). Caused 43,449 errors during backfill. Fix: `ALTER TABLE player_stats_misc ALTER COLUMN hob TYPE numeric(6,4) USING hob::numeric;`\n\n- **players table schema mismatch**: Attempted to INSERT with `jersey_number` column